{"type":"text","timestamp":1775848349379,"sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","part":{"id":"prt_d78cf5b9d001f86mKPKTqZjDiq","messageID":"msg_d78cf4f4b001nFppt9sSX1JcdE","sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","type":"text","text":"I'll create a `design.md` file with technical implementation details for the Router HTTP reverse proxy core feature (AR-009) in the agentcube project.","time":{"start":1775848349377,"end":1775848349377}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848377345,"sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","part":{"id":"prt_d78cf5ec40013cOV8JFRGJWS7p","messageID":"msg_d78cf4f4b001nFppt9sSX1JcdE","sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f7b3e1f57abb4ecbb70bf044","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","content":"# AR-009: Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\nThe Router module (`pkg/router`) acts as an HTTP reverse proxy that routes incoming requests to appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter backends based on Kubernetes CRD resources.\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│   Router     │────▶│  AgentRuntime/      │\n│             │     │  (reverse    │     │  CodeInterpreter    │\n│             │     │   proxy)     │     │  Backend            │\n└─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────────────┘\n                           │\n                           ▼\n                    ┌──────────────┐\n                    │  Kubernetes  │\n                    │  API Server  │\n                    │  (watch CRs) │\n                    └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### Components\n\n1. **Router Server**: Main HTTP server that accepts incoming requests\n2. **Route Resolver**: Determines backend target from request path/headers\n3. **Proxy Handler**: Forwards requests to backend services\n4. **CRD Watcher**: Watches AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs for route updates\n5. **Connection Pool**: Manages reusable backend connections\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### RouteEntry\n```go\ntype RouteEntry struct {\n    Name        string\n    Namespace   string\n    Kind        string // AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n    BackendURL  string\n    Health      HealthStatus\n    LastUpdated time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### RouterConfig\n```go\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    KubeConfig     *rest.Config\n    ListenAddr     string\n    ReadTimeout    time.Duration\n    WriteTimeout   time.Duration\n    IdleTimeout    time.Duration\n    MaxConnections int\n    HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### Router\n```go\ntype Router struct {\n    config         *RouterConfig\n    routes         sync.Map // map[string]*RouteEntry\n    httpClient     *http.Client\n    kubeClient     *versioned.Clientset\n    informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    stopCh         chan struct{}\n    wg             sync.WaitGroup\n}\n```\n\n### HealthStatus\n```go\ntype HealthStatus struct {\n    Healthy   bool\n    LastCheck time.Time\n    Error     error\n    ConsecutiveFailures int\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Incoming Request Format\n\n**Path Pattern:**\n```\n/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/{kind}/{name}\n```\n\n**Headers:**\n- `X-Forwarded-For`: Client IP (auto-added)\n- `X-Real-IP`: Client IP (auto-added)\n- `Host`: Original request host\n\n### Response Handling\n\n**Success:**\n- Status code: Backend response status (2xx, 3xx)\n- Body: Proxied from backend\n- Headers: Merged (hop-by-hop headers removed)\n\n**Error:**\n```go\ntype RouterError struct {\n    Code       int\n    Message    string\n    RouteName  string\n    Reason     string // RouteNotFound, BackendUnavailable, Timeout, etc.\n}\n```\n\n**Error Codes:**\n- `404 Not Found`: Route not found\n- `502 Bad Gateway`: Backend unavailable/unhealthy\n- `503 Service Unavailable`: No healthy backends\n- `504 Gateway Timeout`: Backend timeout\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Route Resolution Errors\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrRouteNotFound      = errors.New(\"route not found\")\n    ErrNoHealthyBackends  = errors.New(\"no healthy backends available\")\n    ErrInvalidRouteKind   = errors.New(\"invalid route kind\")\n)\n```\n\n### Proxy Errors\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrBackendConnection  = errors.New(\"failed to connect to backend\")\n    ErrBackendTimeout     = errors.New(\"backend timeout\")\n    ErrRequestEntityTooLarge = errors.New(\"request entity too large\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Route Not Found**: Return 404 with error body\n2. **Backend Connection Failure**: Retry with next healthy backend (if available)\n3. **All Backends Unhealthy**: Return 503 with circuit breaker status\n4. **Timeout**: Return 504, mark backend as unhealthy\n5. **Context Cancellation**: Abort request, log cancellation reason\n\n### Health Check Failure Policy\n\n- 3 consecutive failures → Mark backend as unhealthy\n- Healthy check interval: 10 seconds\n- Backend removed from rotation until health restored\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File: `pkg/router/router_test.go`**\n\n```go\n// Test cases:\nfunc TestRouter_ResolveRoute(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_ProxyRequest(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_HealthCheck(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_AddRoute(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_RemoveRoute(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_RetryOnFailure(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File: `pkg/router/handler_test.go`**\n\n```go\n// Test cases:\nfunc TestHandler_ServeHTTP_Success(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandler_ServeHTTP_RouteNotFound(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandler_ServeHTTP_BackendError(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandler_ServeHTTP_Timeout(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File: `tests/integration/router_test.go`**\n\n```go\n// Test scenarios:\n// 1. End-to-end request routing with live backends\n// 2. CRD update triggers route refresh\n// 3. Health check removes/adds backends\n// 4. Concurrent request handling under load\n```\n\n### Mock Components\n\n```go\n// Fake Kubernetes client for testing\ntype FakeKubeClient struct {\n    agentcubeFake *fake.Clientset\n}\n\n// Mock backend server for integration tests\ntype MockBackend struct {\n    server   *httptest.Server\n    handler  http.HandlerFunc\n}\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\n// Sample AgentRuntime CR for tests\nvar testAgentRuntime = &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n    ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n        Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    },\n    Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n        BackendURL: \"http://localhost:8080\",\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### Coverage Requirements\n\n- Route resolution: 100%\n- Proxy handler: 100%\n- Health check: 100%\n- Error paths: 100%\n- Overall: ≥85%\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775848377336,"end":1775848377342}}}}
