{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848385479,"sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","part":{"id":"prt_d78cfe729001kve6ZiC6Y9Ngq9","messageID":"msg_d78cfda27001SMKW1PpmaeUF0S","sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_cb96ebf2d1ce45c1a5d5e68f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/workloadmanager/\n13: ├── processor/\n14: │   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n15: │   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n16: │   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n17: ├── types/\n18: │   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n19: └── config/\n20:     └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Integration Points\n24: \n25: - **Client-go**: Uses generated typed client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n26: - **Informers**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` and `AgentRuntime` resources\n27: - **Listers**: Provides cached read access to resources\n28: \n29: ## Data Structures\n30: \n31: ### Sandbox Processor\n32: \n33: ```go\n34: type SandboxProcessor struct {\n35:     client       runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n36:     informer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n37:     lister       runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n38:     config       *SandboxConfig\n39:     eventHandler cache.ResourceEventHandlerRegistration\n40: }\n41: \n42: type SandboxConfig struct {\n43:     DefaultNamespace     string\n44:     ResourceTimeout      time.Duration\n45:     DefaultCPURequest    string\n46:     DefaultMemoryRequest string\n47:     AllowedRuntimes      []string\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Sandbox Context\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: type SandboxContext struct {\n55:     Name         string\n56:     Namespace    string\n57:     RuntimeType  string\n58:     Owner        string\n59:     Labels       map[string]string\n60:     Annotations  map[string]string\n61:     Resources    v1.ResourceRequirements\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## API Contracts\n66: \n67: ### Processor Interface\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: type Processor interface {\n71:     Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n72:     Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n73:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n74:     Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n75:     Watch(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Create Operation\n80: \n81: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with required fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `RuntimeType`\n82: \n83: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n84: \n85: **Behavior**:\n86: 1. Validate sandbox context (required fields, allowed runtime types)\n87: 2. Check for existing sandbox with same name\n88: 3. Construct `CodeInterpreter` object with proper labels/annotations\n89: 4. Apply resource quotas from config\n90: 5. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create()`\n91: 6. Return created resource or error\n92: \n93: ### Update Operation\n94: \n95: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with `Name`, `Namespace`, and fields to update\n96: \n97: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n98: \n99: **Behavior**:\n100: 1. Fetch existing `CodeInterpreter`\n101: 2. Apply updates (resources, labels, annotations)\n102: 3. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update()`\n103: 4. Return updated resource\n104: \n105: ### Delete Operation\n106: \n107: **Input**: `name`, `namespace`\n108: \n109: **Output**: error\n110: \n111: **Behavior**:\n112: 1. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()`\n113: 2. Handle `NotFound` errors gracefully\n114: \n115: ## Error Handling\n116: \n117: ### Error Types\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: var (\n121:     ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n122:     ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"sandbox already exists\")\n123:     ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"invalid runtime type\")\n124:     ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"sandbox validation failed\")\n125:     ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n126: )\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Error Wrapping\n130: \n131: All errors wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`.\n132: \n133: ### Retry Strategy\n134: \n135: - Transient errors: 3 retries with exponential backoff (100ms, 200ms, 400ms)\n136: - `TooManyRequests`: Respect `Retry-After` header\n137: - Permanent errors: Return immediately without retry\n138: \n139: ## Testing Strategy\n140: \n141: ### Unit Tests\n142: \n143: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n144: \n145: **Test Cases**:\n146: 1. `TestCreateSandbox_Success` - Valid sandbox creation\n147: 2. `TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime` - Rejected runtime type\n148: 3. `TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists` - Duplicate creation\n149: 4. `TestUpdateSandbox_Success` - Resource update\n150: 5. `TestDeleteSandbox_Success` - Normal deletion\n151: 6. `TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound` - Idempotent delete\n152: 7. `TestGetSandbox_Success` - Retrieve existing sandbox\n153: \n154: ### Test Fixtures\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: func newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n158:     return &SandboxContext{\n159:         Name:        name,\n160:         Namespace:   \"default\",\n161:         RuntimeType: runtime,\n162:         Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n163:             Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n164:                 v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n165:                 v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n166:             },\n167:         },\n168:     }\n169: }\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Mock Setup\n173: \n174: ```go\n175: func newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n176:     return &SandboxProcessor{\n177:         client: client,\n178:         config: &SandboxConfig{\n179:             DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n180:             ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n181:             AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n182:         },\n183:     }\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Integration Tests\n188: \n189: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_integration_test.go`\n190: \n191: Tests against real Kubernetes cluster (kind) using `envtest`:\n192: 1. Full lifecycle (create → update → delete)\n193: 2. Concurrent operations\n194: 3. Resource quota enforcement\n195: \n196: ## Implementation Notes\n197: \n198: ### Resource Naming\n199: \n200: CodeInterpreter resources follow pattern: `sandbox-{owner}-{uuid}`\n201: \n202: ### Labels\n203: \n204: Standard labels applied to all sandboxes:\n205: - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n206: - `app.kubernetes.io/component: sandbox`\n207: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/owner: <owner>`\n208: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <runtime-type>`\n209: \n210: ### Annotations\n211: \n212: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/created-at: <RFC3339>`\n213: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/last-updated: <RFC3339>`\n214: \n215: ### Timeout Handling\n216: \n217: Creation uses context with timeout from `config.ResourceTimeout`. Watch for resource to reach `Ready` phase within timeout window.\n\n(End of file - total 217 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── processor/\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n│   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n│   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n├── types/\n│   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n└── config/\n    └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775848385450,"end":1775848385473}}}}
