{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775848387265,"sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","part":{"id":"prt_d78cff2c0001fzh43qiMuUwM3P","messageID":"msg_d78cfec01001QGvumWymh24m5J","sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848434646,"sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","part":{"id":"prt_d78cff555001gjAvLZHn3ryCxh","messageID":"msg_d78cfec01001QGvumWymh24m5J","sessionID":"ses_28730c0b2ffe595nJG9uFlAhsc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b8e16f7da9b84f439af9087e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Design: AR-009 Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Router module (`pkg/router`) that acts as an HTTP reverse proxy, routing incoming requests to appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter backends based on Kubernetes CRD resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── router.go                   # Main router implementation\n├── router_test.go             # Unit tests\n├── handler.go                 # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n├── handler_test.go            # Handler tests\n├── resolver.go                # Route resolution logic\n├── resolver_test.go           # Resolver tests\n├── health.go                  # Health check manager\n├── health_test.go             # Health check tests\n├── config.go                  # Configuration structures\n└── types.go                   # Type definitions\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources via `SharedInformerFactory`\n- **Listers**: Provides cached read access for route resolution\n- **HTTP Client**: Reusable connection pool for backend requests\n\n### High-Level Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│   Handler    │────▶│  Resolver   │────▶│  RouteEntry     │\n│             │     │              │     │             │     │  (from routes)  │\n└─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n                           │                                          │\n                           ▼                                          ▼\n                    ┌──────────────┐                          ┌─────────────────┐\n                    │   Router     │                          │  Backend URL    │\n                    │  (manages    │                          │  (proxy target) │\n                    │   routes)    │                          │                 │\n                    └──────────────┘                          └─────────────────┘\n                           │\n                           ▼\n                    ┌──────────────┐\n                    │  Informers   │\n                    │  (watch CRs) │\n                    └──────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Router\n\n```go\ntype Router struct {\n    config          *RouterConfig\n    routes          sync.Map // map[string]*RouteEntry\n    httpClient      *http.Client\n    kubeClient      *versioned.Clientset\n    informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    runtimeInformer v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\n    interpreterInformer v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n    stopCh          chan struct{}\n    wg              sync.WaitGroup\n    mu              sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n\n### RouterConfig\n\n```go\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    KubeConfig          *rest.Config\n    ListenAddr          string\n    ReadTimeout         time.Duration\n    WriteTimeout        time.Duration\n    IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n    MaxConnsPerHost     int\n    HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n    HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n    UnhealthyThreshold  int\n    Namespace           string // empty means all namespaces\n}\n```\n\n### RouteEntry\n\n```go\ntype RouteEntry struct {\n    Name       string\n    Namespace  string\n    Kind       string // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    BackendURL string\n    Health     HealthStatus\n    UpdatedAt  time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### HealthStatus\n\n```go\ntype HealthStatus struct {\n    Healthy             bool\n    LastCheck           time.Time\n    Error               error\n    ConsecutiveFailures int\n    mu                  sync.Mutex\n}\n```\n\n### RouteKey\n\n```go\n// routeKey generates unique key for route storage\nfunc routeKey(namespace, kind, name string) string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s\", namespace, kind, name)\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Incoming Request Format\n\n**Path Pattern:**\n```\n/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/{resourceType}/{name}[/{subpath}]\n```\n\n**Resource Types:**\n- `agentruntimes` → Maps to AgentRuntime CR\n- `codeinterpreters` → Maps to CodeInterpreter CR\n\n**Headers (added by router):**\n- `X-Forwarded-For`: Client IP\n- `X-Real-IP`: Client IP\n- `X-Forwarded-Host`: Original host\n- `X-Forwarded-Proto`: Request scheme\n\n### Processor Interface\n\n```go\ntype RouterInterface interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n    ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n}\n```\n\n### Resolve Operation\n\n**Input**: `*http.Request`\n\n**Output**: `*RouteEntry` or error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Parse namespace, resourceType, name from path\n2. Look up route from `routes` sync.Map\n3. Check backend health status\n4. Return RouteEntry or error\n\n### Proxy Operation\n\n**Input**: `http.ResponseWriter`, `*http.Request`, `*RouteEntry`\n\n**Output**: error\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Build backend URL from RouteEntry.BackendURL\n2. Clone request with new context\n3. Add forwarding headers\n4. Execute request via `httpClient.Do()`\n5. Copy response headers and body\n6. Handle errors appropriately\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrRouteNotFound      = errors.New(\"route not found\")\n    ErrNoHealthyBackends  = errors.New(\"no healthy backends available\")\n    ErrInvalidResourceType = errors.New(\"invalid resource type\")\n    ErrMalformedPath      = errors.New(\"malformed request path\")\n)\n\nvar (\n    ErrBackendConnection  = errors.New(\"failed to connect to backend\")\n    ErrBackendTimeout     = errors.New(\"backend timeout\")\n    ErrBackendUnavailable = errors.New(\"backend unavailable\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```go\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error       string `json:\"error\"`\n    Code        string `json:\"code\"`\n    RouteName   string `json:\"routeName,omitempty\"`\n    Timestamp   string `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n```\n\n### HTTP Status Codes\n\n| Scenario | Status Code |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Route not found | 404 |\n| Invalid resource type | 400 |\n| Malformed path | 400 |\n| Backend unavailable | 502 |\n| No healthy backends | 503 |\n| Backend timeout | 504 |\n\n### Retry Strategy\n\n- **Connection errors**: Retry with next healthy backend (max 2 retries)\n- **Timeout**: Mark backend unhealthy, return 504\n- **Permanent errors** (4xx from backend): Return immediately\n\n### Health Check Failure Policy\n\n```\nConsecutive Failures → Action\n3                   → Mark unhealthy, remove from rotation\n1                   → Continue serving, log warning\nRecovery (1 success) → Mark healthy, restore to rotation\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `router/router_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test cases:\nfunc TestRouter_Start(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_Shutdown(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_ServeHTTP(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestRouter_routeKey(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `router/resolver_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test cases:\nfunc TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Success(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResolver_ResolveRoute_NotFound(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Unhealthy(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestResolver_ParsePath(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `router/health_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test cases:\nfunc TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Success(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Failure(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHealthChecker_MarkUnhealthy(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHealthChecker_MarkHealthy(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n**File**: `router/handler_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test cases:\nfunc TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Success(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandler_ProxyRequest_BackendError(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Timeout(t *testing.T)\nfunc TestHandler_AddForwardingHeaders(t *testing.T)\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestRouteEntry(name, namespace, backendURL string) *RouteEntry {\n    return &RouteEntry{\n        Name:       name,\n        Namespace:  namespace,\n        Kind:       \"AgentRuntime\",\n        BackendURL: backendURL,\n        Health:     HealthStatus{Healthy: true},\n        UpdatedAt:  time.Now(),\n    }\n}\n\nfunc newTestRouterConfig() *RouterConfig {\n    return &RouterConfig{\n        ListenAddr:          \":8080\",\n        ReadTimeout:         15 * time.Second,\n        WriteTimeout:        30 * time.Second,\n        IdleTimeout:         60 * time.Second,\n        HealthCheckInterval: 10 * time.Second,\n        HealthCheckTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n        UnhealthyThreshold:  3,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Mock Setup\n\n```go\n// Fake kube client for testing\nfunc newFakeKubeClient(objects ...runtime.Object) *versioned.Clientset {\n    return fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)\n}\n\n// Mock backend server\nfunc newMockBackend(handler http.HandlerFunc) *httptest.Server {\n    return httptest.NewServer(handler)\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `router/router_integration_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test scenarios (requires kind cluster):\n// 1. CRD creation triggers route addition\n// 2. CRD deletion triggers route removal\n// 3. End-to-end request routing\n// 4. Health check removes unhealthy backend\n// 5. Concurrent request handling\n```\n\n### Coverage Requirements\n\n- Route resolution: 100%\n- Proxy handler: 100%\n- Health check: 100%\n- Error handling paths: 100%\n- Overall: ≥85%\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Route Key Format\n\nRoutes stored in sync.Map with key: `{namespace}/{kind}/{name}`\n- Kind is lowercased: `agentruntime` or `codeinterpreter`\n\n### Labels Monitored\n\nInformer filters resources with labels:\n- `agentcube.volcano.sh/expose: \"true\"` (only exposed resources are routed)\n\n### Backend URL Discovery\n\nBackend URL extracted from CR spec:\n- AgentRuntime: `.spec.endpoint`\n- CodeInterpreter: `.spec.serviceURL`\n\n### Connection Pooling\n\nHTTP client configured with:\n```go\n&http.Transport{\n    MaxConnsPerHost:     config.MaxConnsPerHost,\n    MaxIdleConns:        100,\n    MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 10,\n    IdleConnTimeout:     90 * time.Second,\n}\n```\n\n### Graceful Shutdown\n\n1. Stop accepting new connections\n2. Close idle connections\n3. Wait for in-flight requests (max 30s)\n4. Stop informers\n5. Close Kubernetes client\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md","time":{"start":1775848434622,"end":1775848434643}}}}
